# Design Tokens

Tokens are the design system's source of truth for colours, spacing, typography, and other visual constants.

## Active Project Tokens

Live at `tokens/design-tokens.json` (path configured in `studio.config.json`).

## Token Categories

```json
{
  "color": {
    "primary": { "value": "#6366f1" },
    "secondary": { "value": "#8b5cf6" },
    "background": { "value": "#ffffff" },
    "foreground": { "value": "#09090b" },
    "muted": { "value": "#f4f4f5" },
    "border": { "value": "#e4e4e7" }
  },
  "spacing": {
    "xs": { "value": "4px" },
    "sm": { "value": "8px" },
    "md": { "value": "16px" },
    "lg": { "value": "24px" },
    "xl": { "value": "32px" }
  },
  "typography": {
    "heading": { "fontSize": { "value": "24px" }, "fontWeight": { "value": "700" } },
    "body": { "fontSize": { "value": "16px" }, "fontWeight": { "value": "400" } }
  },
  "borderRadius": {
    "sm": { "value": "4px" },
    "md": { "value": "8px" },
    "lg": { "value": "12px" }
  },
  "shadow": {
    "sm": { "value": "0 1px 2px rgba(0,0,0,0.05)" },
    "md": { "value": "0 4px 6px -1px rgba(0,0,0,0.1)" }
  }
}
```

## Referencing Tokens in Specs

In node `style` objects, use `$` prefix:
- `"$color.primary"` → resolves to `#6366f1`
- `"$spacing.md"` → resolves to `16px`
- `"$borderRadius.lg"` → resolves to `12px`

## DS Starter Presets

Pre-built token sets live in `spec/ds-starters/`:
- `shadcn.tokens.json` — shadcn/ui defaults
- `material3-web.tokens.json` — Material Design 3
- `ant-design.tokens.json` — Ant Design
- `ios-hig.tokens.json` — Apple HIG

## Theme Structure

The DS supports multiple themes. Each theme is a complete set of token overrides:

```json
{
  "themes": {
    "light": { "color": { "background": { "value": "#ffffff" } } },
    "dark": { "color": { "background": { "value": "#09090b" } } }
  }
}
```

## Token → CSS Variable Bridge

At runtime, tokens are converted to CSS custom properties:
- `$color.primary` → `var(--color-primary)`
- `$spacing.md` → `var(--spacing-md)`

The compiler emits these variables at build time.
